fields.value: Curiosity spent sols 57 to 100 at this location collecting and processing five scoops of loose, unconsolidated materials extracted from an aeolian sand shadow. Scoops 1 and 2 were processed by CHIMRA and discarded to reduce any terrestrial organic contamination that may have remained after a thorough cleaning on Earth and to coat and passivate the interior surfaces of the collection device with Mars dust. Portions (40 to 50 mg) of scoops 3 and 4 were delivered to the Chemistry and Mineralogy (CheMin) instrument.

This table contains mineral abundances and analytical errors derived from diffraction-all K-alpha diffraction data for the fifth  scooped soil sample from the Rocknest target, analyzed in CheMin cell number 7a (Mylar window). The analysis is based on the level 1B EDR file CMA_405889312RDA00950050104CH11504P1. Mineral identifications, abundances and analytical errors for crystalline phases were determined using the program TOPAS.  In addition to the crystalline phases, a broad rise in background is present and has been modeled using the program FULLPAT to indicate that ~29 +/- 10 weight% of this sample consists of X-ray amorphous material; a small amount of this may consist of allophane-like material. Column 1 of the table lists mineral identifications, column 2 lists the mineral abundances in weight percent, and column 3 indicates the estimated 2-sigma analytical errors.

Errors shown in column 3 are 1-sigma and include the combined instrumental error plus analytical error estimated from seven separate JADE analyses by members of the CheMin team. In Marimba2 the combined errors in pyroxene abundance produce a 1-sigma error comparable to the estimated abundance, but analysis of the full four nights of Marimba2 data in CMB_524082694RDA14260561236CH00113P2 confirms that pyroxene is present.
